layout.p:
Columns: 3;
                                                  ruled lines: 28;
                                                  written lines: 27; Uniform layout. Judges, Ezekiel, Obadiah and Nahum commence a new column; Jeremiah, Hosea, Ruth and Daniel open a new leaf. The first word of each book is written in large ornamental characters. At the beginning of different books the masorah is written in ornamental designs. The catchwords are enclosed within a pen and ink design. The running titles of the books are written in cursive German characters in the upper left corner of the recto of each book. The leaves are numbered with ordinary ciphers in the lower right-hand corner of each verso and the Latin titles of the books and the numbers of the chapters are written at the foot of each recto. In the text, the chapters are numbered with ciphers throughout the whole manuscript. Pricking and ruling (with hard-point on the hair side of the folio) are visible.
